Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper focuses on the performance evaluation of a commercial adaptive cruise control system, which is a control system for vehicles. The paper also discusses the string stability of the system, which is a concept related to control systems. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with the performance evaluation of an automated driving system, which is a type of robot. The paper also discusses the car following model, which is a common topic in robotics research. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses data collected from a commercial adaptive cruise control system to calibrate a car following model. This involves machine learning techniques and optimization algorithms, which are common in AI research. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses data collected from a commercial adaptive cruise control system to calibrate a car following model. This involves machine learning techniques and optimization algorithms, which are common in machine learning research. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses field data to evaluate the performance of a commercial adaptive cruise control system and to calibrate a car following model. This involves computational techniques and engineering principles, which are common in computational engineering research.
